##During the most tense week in Wuhan, online consultations have proliferated across the country

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. Affected by the epidemic, many medical insurance rapid opening of Internet medical payment business, but this may be far from the spring of the industry, the long-term "share of health insurance" is still a bottleneck, to find other buyers are also exploring the period

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Xin Ying and Yu Yan, CAIJING reporters

Editor | Wang Xiao

"My most memorable online question was, what if a bat flew into the house? "

A doctor at the Union Medical College Hospital in Wuhan encountered this problem during an online consultation. He and his colleagues, in Wuhan Medical Resources at the most tense moment, the battlefield moved to the Internet.

On January 22, on the eve of the city closure in Wuhan, a large number of patients were waiting in the designated hospital for new pneumonia and the fever outpatient hospital. "people are so nervous that they run to the hospital for minor colds, and when they find that a hospital near their home is not available for treatment, they move on to the next hospital, " the Wuhan Union Hospital told Caijing, unfortunately, in the early morning of January 23, received a hospital notice, asked him to quarantine at home, "a few days ago to eat with colleagues were diagnosed with infection. ".

With doctors hard to reach and patients piling up in hospitals, the Wuhan Union Hospital has called on doctors who have the time to offer consultations on the APP, without rigid division of departments, every doctor acts as a general practitioner.

The wuhan-based doctor, who had been providing online consultation services on a national Internet platform for two years, used his hospital's online APP for the first time, "do I need to go to the hospital? " It was the question he had to answer the most. And he also had a lot of frustration with the medical advice, "people with fevers below 38.5 degrees are advised to take medication and to be isolated at home. Going to the hospital increases the risk of cross-infection and there is also a risk of infection at home, but this was really not an option at the time. ".

Every morning at 8:30 am, the Wuhan Xiehe doctor can receive about 70 patients online a day. That's about as efficient as his hospital visits. At the time, however, the APP didn't have the ability to write prescriptions. According to the new national scheme of diagnosis and treatment of pneumonia, he will recommend patients to take oral antiviral drugs and so on, let patients buy their own, "but then some patients have feedback can not buy drugs. ".

Not only in Wuhan, the first week after the Spring Festival, but also the national outbreak of online consultation week. "The system has never experienced such a high volume of one-day visits, " Cheng Yi, senior vice president of micro-medicine, told CAIJING.

At this point, the core need for online counseling is for people who have fever and cough-related symptoms, but are afraid to go to the hospital. "Many of the consultants were in the epidemic area and didn't dare go to the hospital or were too scared, " said Gui Hongzhen, a former deputy director of the Beijing military general hospital who worked with Xiaotangshan to fight SARS, according to the Atypical pneumonia, one of them, in the course of an online consultation, had apparently developed symptoms of new pneumonia, but did not want to go to the hospital, fearing that people would look at him differently. "We helped him to contact the local hospital, and at the same time we tried to persuade him, " he said.

According to the COVID-19, the biggest concern for online consultations is how to identify and prevent the disease. Of those, 40 percent were concerned about preventing coronavirus infection; 25 percent asked whether a fever, dry cough, or weakness meant they had contracted a new coronavirus; and 10 percent asked how COVID-19 was transmitted.

As the outbreak has progressed, the pressure to see a doctor in Wuhan has shifted to ordinary residents who have been confined to their homes by their communities. The advantage of Internet + medical treatment, highlight in this special period.

Micro-medical, ping 'an good doctor and other platforms have been launched on the epidemic consultation zone, free of charge for patients with new pneumonia consultation. During the outbreak, the number of daily visits in the area increased by 10 times, the number of new registered users of the APP increased by 10 times, and the daily average consultation volume was 9 times that of normal times.

On March 5, the long-awaited "opinions on deepening the reform of the Health Care System" (hereinafter referred to as the "opinions") was officially released. This blockbuster document makes clear to the Internet + Health Care Business, it is necessary to adapt to the development of internet + medical service mode from the budget management of Medical Insurance Fund and the selection of appointed institutions of medical insurance.

Perhaps take the opportunity of epidemic situation, will ask a doctor in Internet hospital to Include Medical Insurance to pay promotion to come.

It's never easy to get medicine online

"I successfully ordered medicine online. " At 8 pm on March 2, Ren Yi (not his real name) , a 72-year-old Wuhan resident, used his mobile phone to buy his own life-saving medicine, the first day of the emergency launch of the electronic certificate of State Medical Insurance in Wuhan.

National Health Insurance Electronic Voucher in Wuhan on-line, but also to respond to the needs of Wuhan epidemic, open online consultation, prescription circulation, offline drug delivery, medical insurance reimbursement of the whole process of the last link.

On Feb. 24, patients with 10 kinds of serious chronic diseases such as hypertension and diabetes could use the medical insurance card to consult online in three public hospitals: Wuhan Union Hospital, People's Hospital of Wuhan University and Central Hospital of Wuhan. February 26, a platform-based micro-medical Internet general hospital was added. The Wuhan Health Insurance Bureau pays directly for all four online clinics.

"If it were not for the special circumstances of the epidemic, the policy of opening the Internet to medical care would not have been rolled out so quickly, " Zhu Minglai, director of the Nankai University, told Caijing.

Ren Yi had to take Atorvastatin for a long time because of his heart stent operation. After the outbreak of the disease, traffic in Wuhan City was suspended, the whole community closed management, Ren Yi's children can not help, he had to find their own way to buy medicine.

Community workers have sent a car to take Ren Yi to the hospital for medicine, but the hospital has become a new crown pneumonia designated hospital, general outpatient clinic suspended, and to the hospital, but also worried about increasing the risk of infection. Community workers can also help to go to the pharmacy to buy, but it is too busy, sometimes by mistake.

Ren Yi's dilemma is also the one facing nearly 400,000 people with severe chronic diseases in Wuhan.

The First Time Ren Yi bought medicine on his own on the micro-medical platform, he failed because he needed face recognition, and the operation could not be performed by his children on his behalf, even though he often used smartphones and uploaded case information, etc. , it's not easy for a 72-year-old man. Finally, with the help of the customer service staff, Ren Yi successfully placed the order for the second time.

Wuhan micro-medical Internet Hospital on the first day of the launch of nearly 20,000 prescriptions, the pressure of offline audit. Because patients with social security cards buy drugs online, and the health insurance system is not open, online drug purchase system can not automatically connect patients'personal information and health insurance accounts, need to be manually reviewed, the review process takes an average of five to seven minutes per patient.

Finally, the State Medical Insurance Bureau stepped in and overnight guided Wuhan to complete the docking of the state medical insurance electronic credential system, officially go online, open the data, verify identity through face recognition and other means, thus reducing part of the off-line Medical Insurance Verification Process, improve overall efficiency.

"In fact, it is the most difficult to break down the cognitive barriers of internet-based medicine, including the cognition of ordinary patients and doctors, as well as that of policy makers. The epidemic is an opportunity, " a senior Internet medical official told CAIJING, yinchuan, for example, has previously introduced health insurance payments for internet-based hospitals, which can be reimbursed using individual health insurance accounts and hospital outpatient co-ordination accounts, but due to user habits, reimbursement rates, operating procedures and other issues, this has not led to massive user growth.

It is one of the reasons that many patients tend to purchase medicine in hospital. Before Wuhan's Central Hospital started paying for Health Insurance Online, only a dozen purchases and deliveries were made online each day, the Hubei Daily reported. On February 24th, the day of inclusion, 50 prescriptions were delivered online.

On-line platform can implement 24-hour admission. "A doctor who supported us in Africa told us that we have time difference, and we can just form a relay with doctors in China, " said Cheng Yi, when micro-medical's "new pneumonia real-time rescue platform" was launched, only 1,500 specialists, including respiratory specialists, have been recruited and called on by the Health Commission, and the number has risen to more than 40,000.

This is not only a breakthrough in policy, but also a comprehensive examination of Internet diagnosis and treatment.

Online consultation platform in Wuhan epidemic in the power to rely on the reimbursement of health insurance department support. "micro-medical first phase with 8 designated medical insurance qualified (Wuhan) pharmacies offline cooperation, prescription circulation, drug supply, medical insurance payment go overall account reimbursement. " Cheng Yi introduced.

Wuhan Union Hospital's APP has also opened up online prescriptions, and features such as health insurance are being refined.

Outside Wuhan, an Internet hospital official who is docking with the local health insurance bureau told CAIJING that although all parties are speeding up, from obtaining an Internet hospital license to completing the docking of the online system for health insurance payment, it's still nearly two months away.

WHO GETS THE SHARE OF HEALTH INSURANCE?

The Wuhan Union doctor, who has stopped online consultations, found that "effective" problems were significantly reduced. As Wuhan's local hospitals, quarantine sites and doctors around the country rushed to their aid, the shortage of medical resources eased, and the number of people coming online for advice on suspected symptoms plummeted. This means that the situation is no longer stressful and time has to be allowed for more patients who really need it.

That's why the Wuhan based Xiehe doctor stopped using the Internet two years ago, when he encountered fewer and fewer patients of his specialty online.

When the epidemic is over, it will return to the real state of the industry. Ju Ming argues that Internet based medicine is, after all, a new way to get things done. It can be done with new services, like delivering medicine to your door, but who pays for the delivery, how To digest the new value is the industry based on long-term development of the key.

As China's largest pharmaceutical market to pay the bill, the large entrance of medical insurance into the Internet medical treatment let people full of expectations. But under the overall environment of medical insurance control fee, how much share can Internet hospital get in the overall medical insurance market?

The above Internet medical senior personage analysis, regarding the Internet hospital reimbursement, if the medical insurance opens the individual account, it is crowding out the market of the pharmacy, if it is using the medical insurance pool account which is used for the outpatient service and the hospitalization reimbursement, is the amount of money that the hospital advances. "during the outbreak period, it was fine, but after that, the hospital had to consider its own offline operations, in-patient services, and would certainly balance the online quota, " he said.

Health insurance is also raising the level of co-ordination of funds, but it is still the city-level co-ordination, how much to open up by local decision-making impact. And local policymakers are indeed hesitant.

A staff member of Liaoning provincial local health insurance bureau told CAIJING that integrating internet-based health care into health insurance is a supply-side reform, but he is more concerned about how many patients'needs can be met.

"My district has a pharmacy every 100 meters, almost all of which are health insurance designated pharmacies, which do not rest during the Spring Festival, and even during the epidemic, residents are not affected to buy medicine. It does have several Internet hospitals, but few residents know about them, and even fewer need them. And the standards, norms and pricing of online medical services are not clear, which is one of the reasons for our hesitancy.

Zhu Minglai also believes that if the primary health care system is well developed, residents can easily go out to meet the demand for medical treatment. "To be honest, I don't think there are any development opportunities for internet-based medical care. ".

But in the reality patient unceasingly gathers to the three first-class hospitals, the medical treatment cost is higher and higher. The weakness of grading diagnosis and treatment at the grass-roots level is the real development space of Internet hospital in Zhu Minglai's eyes. It can make up the shortage of offline medical resources by coordinating online resources, we may one day be able to provide us with health management value-added services of the family doctor, by our own online choice. A full range of online services, in order to retain the most extensive doctor resources.

At present, a number of online consultation platform will still be their next major business in chronic diseases, common diseases and follow-up prescription.

"health care can't afford everything, so whether consumer habits will change in the future, or whether commercial insurance will be willing to pay for medical value-added services on the Internet, that needs to be explored, " Zhu said.

The Universal Medical Security System should be multi-level. The State Medical Insurance Bureau also pointed out that by 2030, basic medical insurance should be the main body, and medical assistance should be the base, a multi-level medical security system developed together with Supplementary Medical Insurance, Commercial Health Insurance, charitable donations and mutual medical assistance.

Commercial Insurance is already exploring the possibilities. Zoomlion obtained its Internet hospital licence in July 2019 and went live in late December of the same year. By connecting Internet insurance to internet-related Hospital Services, Zhong an forms a closed loop of medical services internally.

When public hospitals and platform-based Internet companies stand on the race track of Internet hospitals at the same time, "what they really strive for is service, " several industry insiders pointed out to the reporter from Caijing that the real advantage of internet-based medical care lies in its online operation ability, and public hospitals, especially the third-level hospitals, have been "overcrowded" , their online investment is not considerable, long-term competitiveness is still limited.

Although Cheng Yi is more confident about the normalization of Internet medicine, she is also aware that the value of Internet medicine can only be fully realized if all the medical, testing, medicine, insurance and data are connected, to move their business from offline to online.
